Two former Manchester United players are expected to sign for Juventus this week. According to transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano, Paul Pogba and Angel Di Maria will join the Serie A giants. Both Pogba and Di Maria will arrive as free agents after leaving United and Paris Saint-Germain, respectively. Romano tweeted: “New Juventus top signings, coming to Italy this week. “Ángel Di María will be in Turin tomorrow night as he will undergo medical tests on Friday. Here we go confirmed today morning. “Paul Pogba will undergo medical tests and sign the contract on Saturday.”